  carbohydrates: 40 g
  protein: 18 g
servings: 2
---

Cut the @new potatoes{1}(cut in half) and place in a #pot of cold water with @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil over medium-high heat. Once the potatoes are boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for ~{20-25%minutes} or until the potatoes are tender.

Cut off the root and then chop the @spring greens{1}(chopped into 2cm chunks). Rinse in a #colander under cold water and keep to one side.

Cut the woody ends off the @rhubarb{1}(chopped into 2cm pieces). Cut the roots off the @spring onion{3}(cut and finely chopped).

Once you've finished your chopping, pre-heat your #grill to medium. Season the @pork chops{2} with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Massage this into the pork chops and cook under the grill for ~{15%minutes}. Turn the pork chops after ~{7-8%minutes} and cook until the meat is white in the centre.

Whilst the pork is under the grill, cook the rhubarb. Heat a #saucepan over medium-high heat and add @water{1%tbsp}. Once hot, add the rhubarb and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Add in @sugar{3%tbsp} and continue cooking until the rhubarb is tender and nicely glazed. Remove the rhubarb from the pan.

> Rhubarb overcooks very quickly and will continue cooking once out of the pan. Stop cooking just as it begins to soften.

Check the potatoes and when tender add the spring greens to the same pot. Cover with a #lid and continue cooking for ~{3%minutes}. Drain in a colander and allow the steam to escape for ~{2%minutes}. Return the potatoes and spring greens to the pot, away from the heat and mash with a #potato masher{}. Stir in half the @creme fraiche{1/2}, chopped spring onions and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Cover to keep warm.

Once the pork chops are cooked, allow them to rest for ~{2%minutes} whilst you make the crème fraîche sauce. Place the remaining @creme fraiche{1/2} into a #small saucepan and stir in @wholegrain mustard{1%tbsp}. Heat gently until hot.

Serve each pork chop on top of a generous pile of the champ potatoes, place a few pieces of glazed rhubarb around the plate and finish with the sauce. Enjoy!